OL,3,CJust how bad has Sheffield United's
OL,4,Cseason been?
OL,6,FThose results make United only the
OL,7,Fthird team in Premier League history
OL,8,Fto concede at least five goals on six
OL,9,Foccasions in the same season.
OL,11,FThey have lost 24 times this season,
OL,12,Fmeaning they could finish with 28
OL,13,Fdefeats if they lose their remaining
OL,14,Fgames. That means they will definitely
OL,15,Favoid the highest number of defeats in
OL,16,Fa single Premier League season, which
OL,17,Fstands at 29 ` a record they already
OL,18,Fshare with Ipswich (1994-95),
OL,19,FSunderland (2005-06) and Derby (2007-
OL,20,F08). United lost that number in 2020-
OL,21,F21.
